<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Photomicrographs of in vivo and protargol stained specimens of Epistylis smalli n. sp. A. General view of a colony of E. smalli. B. Detail of the zooid. The arrow shows the elevated epistomial disk, and the arrow head shows the thick peristomial lip. C. Detail of the zooid showing the C-shaped macronucleus (arrow). D. Protargol stained zooids showing the macronucelus. E. Protargol stained zooid showing the infundibular polykinetid 1. F. Protargol stained zooid showing the infundibular polykinetid 2. G. Protargol stained zooid showing OPK 3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

